{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Les données régionales sur les grandes cultures présentent les estimations de superficie ensemencée et récoltée, de rendement et de production pour la plupart des principales grandes cultures et pour certaines cultures spéciales au Canada. La plupart des régions de données intra-provinciales (RDIP) correspondent exactement aux limites des régions agricoles de recensement (RAR), à l’exception de certaines régions du Québec (où les régions sont définies par les limites administratives provinciales), de la Saskatchewan (où les régions coïncident avec les limites des divisions de recensement à partir de 2017) et de la Colombie-Britannique.  \n  \n  Pour les correspondances exactes entre les régions agricoles de recensement (RAR) et les régions de données intra-provinciales (RDIP), veuillez-vous référer au lien suivant :  \n  \n  https://www.statcan.gc.ca/fra/programmes-statistiques/document/3401_D2_V2", "en": "Small area data (SAD) on field crops show seeded and harvested area, yield and production estimates for most principal field crops and some special crops in Canada. Most SAD geographies correspond exactly with the Census Agriculture Region (CAR) limits, excepts for some regions of Quebec (where small areas are defined by provincial administrative boundaries), Saskatchewan (where small areas coincide with census divisions boundaries as of 2017) and British Columbia.  \n  \n  For exact correspondence between Census Agricultural Regions (CAR) and Small Area Data (SAD) Regions, see the following link:  \n  \n  https://www.statcan.gc.ca/eng/statistical-programs/document/3401_D2_V2"}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "INFOSTATS", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca", "position_name": {"fr": "Renseignements généraux", "en": "General enquiries"}, "frequency": "as_needed", "keywords": {"fr": ["Agriculture", "Limites", "Grandes cultures", "Valeur", "Cartographie", "Archives cartographiques", "Carte"], "en": ["Agriculture", "Boundaries", "Crops", "Value", "Mapping", "Cartographic records", "Maps"]}, "ready_to_publish": "true", "id": "65f1cde1-95e0-4a1d-9a1a-c45b2f83a351", "subject": ["agriculture"], "spatial_representation_type": ["vector"], "distributor": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"organization_name\": \"Gouvernement du Canada; Statistique Canada\", \"phone\": \"1-800-263-1136 (sans frais)\", \"address\": \"150, promenade Tunney's Pasture\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\", \"organization_name\": \"Government of Canada; Statistics Canada\", \"phone\": \"1-800-263-1136 (toll free)\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0T6\", \"address\": \"150 Tunney's Pasture Driveways\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}}", "contact_information": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"delivery_point\": \"150, promenade Tunney's Pasture\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\", \"country\": \"Canada\"}, \"en\": {\"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0T6\", \"delivery_point\": \"150 Tunney's Pasture Driveways\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}}", "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-143.782063,40.184321],[-46.38161,40.184321],[-46.38161,62.281322],[-143.782063,62.281322],[-143.782063,40.184321]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "1976-01-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Régions de données intra-provinciales (RDIP) historiques et actuelles", "en": "Historical and actual Small Area Data (SAD) Regions"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/Agriculture_Agriculture/