{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Cet ensemble de données est formé de polygones qui représentent les aires de drainage des stations de débit actives de l’Aire de drainage du Nord du Québec et du Labrador. En partenariat avec les provinces et territoires et avec d’autres organisations, la Division des relevés hydrologiques du Canada (DRHC) exploite un réseau de plus de 2 600 jauges hydrométriques situées partout au pays. Les polygones du SHN sont une compilation des ensembles de données obtenus de plusieurs organisations participantes, y compris des provinces, des territoires et d’autres ministères. Le personnel d’Environnement et Changement climatique Canada de plusieurs bureaux au pays est aussi responsable de la dérivation de parties importantes de l’ensemble de données. Les utilisateurs doivent savoir que les aires de drainage dérivées de ces polygones pourraient différer des valeurs de superficie brute du bassin versant  officielles des stations hydrométriques publiées par la DRHC.", "en": "This dataset consists of a set of polygons that represent the drainage areas of active discharge stations within the Northern Quebec and Labrador Drainage Area.  \n  \n  In partnership with the provinces, territories and other agencies, the Water Survey of Canada (WSC) operates a network of over 2600 active hydrometric gauges across the country. The NHS Basin Polygon dataset is compilation of datasets collected from a number of contributing agencies, including provinces, territories and other government departments. Environment and Climate Change Canada staff in a number of offices across the country is also responsible for the derivation of large parts of the dataset. Users should be aware that drainage areas derived from these polygons may differ from official drainage areas of hydrometric stations published by WSC."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "Environment and Climate Change Canada", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "erika.klyszejko@canada.ca", "position_name": {"fr": "Centre de renseignements", "en": "Inquiry Centre"}, "frequency": "irregular", "keywords": {"fr": ["Délimitation de bassin", "Eau - quantité", "Fournir des services et des produits d'information sur la quantité d'eau", "Livrer aux clients des produits et des services liés à la quantité d'eau", "L'eau - Aire de drainage principale - Provinces Maritimes", "Environnement", "Système d'information géographique", "Hydrologie", "Eaux intérieures", "Bassin hydrologique"], "en": ["Basin delineation", "Water - Quantity", "Provide Water Quantity Information Products and Services", "Deliver Water Quantity Products and Services to Clients", "Water - Major drainage area - Maritime Provinces", "Environment", "Geographic information systems", "Hydrology", "Inland waters", "Watersheds"]}, "ready_to_publish": "true", "id": "23ec6e7a-b3d0-4419-8604-6159b111a408", "subject": ["nature_and_environment"], "spatial_representation_type": ["vector"], "distributor": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"country\": \"\", \"organization_name\": \"Gouvernement du Canada; Environnement et Changement climatique Canada\", \"phone\": \"819-997-2800\", \"address\": \"10 Wellington, 23rd Floor\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"city\": \"Gatineau\", \"country\": \"\", \"organization_name\": \"Government of Canada; Environment and Climate Change Canada\", \"phone\": \"819-997-2800\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0H3\", \"address\": \"10 Wellington, 23rd Floor\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca\"}}", "contact_information": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"delivery_point\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"erika.klyszejko@canada.ca\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\"}, \"en\": {\"city\": \"\", \"administrative_area\": \"\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"postal_code\": \"\", \"delivery_point\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"erika.klyszejko@canada.ca\"}}", "parent_id": "0c121878-ac23-46f5-95df-eb9960753375", "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-79.765427,47.779313],[-55.573578,47.779313],[-55.573578,62.585182],[-79.765427,62.585182],[-79.765427,47.779313]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "2016-08-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage du Nord du Québec et du Labrador – polygones des bassins du Réseau hydrométrique national", "en": "Northern Quebec and Labrador Drainage Area - National hydrometric network basin polygons"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "https://ec.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/BasinDelineation/MapServer/494", "name_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage du nord du Quebec et Labrador", "en": "Northern Quebec and Labrador Drainage Area"}, "language": ["en"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}, {"url": "https://ec.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/BasinDelineation/MapServer/494", "name_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage du nord du Quebec et Labrador", "en": "Northern Quebec and Labrador Drainage Area"}, "language": ["fr"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}], "status": "ongoing", "source_metadata_date_created": "2018-11-02", "topic_category": ["inland_waters"], "restrictions": "unrestricted", "aggregate_identifier": "", "responsible_role": "RI_418", "collection": "fgp", "date_published": "2016-08-29", "display_flags": ["fgp_viewer"], "file_id": "23ec6e7a-b3d0-4419-8604-6159b111a408", "license_id": "ca-ogl-lgo", "hierarchy_level": "dataset; jeuDonnées", "owner_org": "ec", "metadata_contact": {"fr": "Gouvernement du Canada; Environnement et Changement climatique Canada,enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca", "en": "Government of Canada; Environment and Climate Change Canada,819-997-2800,enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca"}}
{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Cet ensemble de données est formé de polygones qui représentent les aires de drainage des stations de débit actives de l’Aire de drainage de la rivière Yukon. En partenariat avec les provinces et territoires et avec d’autres organisations, la Division des relevés hydrologiques du Canada (DRHC) exploite un réseau de plus de 2 600 jauges hydrométriques situées partout au pays. Les polygones du SHN sont une compilation des ensembles de données obtenus de plusieurs organisations participantes, y compris des provinces, des territoires et d’autres ministères. Le personnel d’Environnement et Changement climatique Canada de plusieurs bureaux au pays est aussi responsable de la dérivation de parties importantes de l’ensemble de données. Les utilisateurs doivent savoir que les aires de drainage dérivées de ces polygones pourraient différer des valeurs de superficie brute du bassin versant officielles des stations hydrométriques publiées par la DRHC.", "en": "This dataset consists of a set of polygons that represent the drainage areas of active discharge stations within the Yukon River Drainage Area.  \n  \n  In partnership with the provinces, territories and other agencies, the Water Survey of Canada (WSC) operates a network of over 2600 active hydrometric gauges across the country. The NHS Basin Polygon dataset is compilation of datasets collected from a number of contributing agencies, including provinces, territories and other government departments. Environment and Climate Change Canada staff in a number of offices across the country is also responsible for the derivation of large parts of the dataset. Users should be aware that drainage areas derived from these polygons may differ from official drainage areas of hydrometric stations published by WSC."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "Environment and Climate Change Canada", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "erika.klyszejko@canada.ca", "position_name": {"fr"