, "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-145.437273,58.860478],[-129.159682,58.860478],[-129.159682,69.082209],[-145.437273,69.082209],[-145.437273,58.860478]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "2016-08-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage de la rivière Yukon – polygones des bassins du Réseau hydrométrique national", "en": "Yukon River Drainage Area - National hydrometric network basin polygons"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "https://ec.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/BasinDelineation/MapServer/1547", "name_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage de la riviere Yukon", "en": "Yukon River Drainage Area"}, "language": ["en"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}, {"url": "https://ec.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/BasinDelineation/MapServer/1238", "name_translated": {"fr": "Aire de drainage de la riviere Yukon", "en": "Yukon River Drainage Area"}, "language": ["fr"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}], "status": "ongoing", "source_metadata_date_created": "2018-11-02", "topic_category": ["inland_waters"], "restrictions": "unrestricted", "aggregate_identifier": "", "responsible_role": "RI_418", "collection": "fgp", "date_published": "2016-08-29", "display_flags": ["fgp_viewer"], "file_id": "534016f1-59c7-4393-96cb-06d53822574b", "license_id": "ca-ogl-lgo", "hierarchy_level": "dataset; jeuDonnées", "owner_org": "ec", "metadata_contact": {"fr": "Gouvernement du Canada; Environnement et Changement climatique Canada,enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca", "en": "Government of Canada; Environment and Climate Change Canada,819-997-2800,enviroinfo@ec.gc.ca"}}
{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Cet ensemble de données comprend des mesures de gestion par zone, qui constituent « d'autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone » (« autres mesures ») selon les Directives opérationnelles du MPO pour déterminer les « autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone » dans le milieu marin du Canada. Il contient également des renseignements au sujet de ces « autres mesures », plus particulièrement leurs noms, leur taille, leurs objectifs, leurs interdictions connexes, et la région du MPO visée.  \n  \n  La détermination des mesures de conservation actuelles et l'établissement de nouvelles « autres mesures » sont des éléments importants de la stratégie du Canada pour atteindre ses objectifs de conservation marine, lesquels prévoient que l'on protège 5 % des zones marines et côtières du Canada d'ici 2017, et 10 % d'ici 2020.   \n  \n  Les « autres mesures » seront évaluées régulièrement, en tenant compte des plus récents renseignements disponibles. De plus, de nouvelles « autres mesures » seront déterminées ou établies au fil du temps. Par conséquent, cet ensemble de données pourrait être modifié avec le temps, et est considéré comme étant actuel selon sa date de publication inscrite.  \n  \n  Les limites et les attributs contenus dans cet ensemble de données sont destinés à fournir une représentation visuelle de la zone et sont à titre informatif seulement. Ils ne devraient pas être considérés comme étant des éléments faisant légalement autorité. Veuillez communiquer avec votre agent des pêches local pour obtenir les coordonnées officielles et des renseignements sur ces fermetures.", "en": "This dataset contains area-based management measures that constitute 'other effective area-based conservation measures' ('other measures') according to DFO's Operational Guidance for Identifying ‘Other Effective Area-Based Conservation Measures’ in Canada’s Marine Environment. It also contains basic information about these ‘other measures’, specifically their names, size, objectives, associated prohibitions, and DFO region.  \n  \n  The identification of existing, and establishment of new, 'other  measures' is an important element of Canada’s strategy to meet its marine conservation targets to protect 5 percent of Canada’s marine and coastal areas by 2017 and 10 percent by 2020.   \n  \n  'Other measures' will be evaluated regularly, taking the most recent available information into account. In addition new 'other measures' will be identified or established over time. Therefore, this data set may change over time, and is considered current as of its publication date stamp.  \n  \n  The boundaries and attributes in this dataset are intended to provide a visual representation of the area and are for information purposes only, and should not be considered legally authoritative. Please contact your local fishery officer for official coordinates and information about these closures."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "Carissa Philippe", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca", "position_name": {"fr": "Analyste de SIG", "en": "GIS Analyst"}, "frequency": "as_needed", "keywords": {"fr": ["Refuges marins", "Aire marine de conservation", "Conservation", "Aire de conservation", "Gestion des pêches", "Pêcheries", "Ressources halieutiques"], "en": ["Marine Refuges", "Marine conservation areas", "Conservation", "Conservation areas", "Fisheries management", "Fisheries", "Fisheries resources"]}, "ready_to_publish": "true", "id": "44769543-7a23-4991-a53f-c2cf7c7a946f", "subject": ["nature_and_environment"], "spatial_representation_type": ["vector"], "distributor": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"organization_name\": \"Gouvernement du Canada; P\\u00eaches et Oc\\u00e9ans Canada; Gestion int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e des oc\\u00e9ans/Politiques des oc\\u00e9ans et des p\\u00eaches/Gestion des \\u00e9cosyst\\u00e8mes et des p\\u00eaches\", \"phone\": \"613-404-5371\", \"address\": \"200 rue Kent\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"organization_name\": \"Government of Canada; Fisheries and Oceans Canada; Integrated Oceans Management/Oceans and Fisheries Policy\", \"phone\": \"613-404-5371\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0E6\", \"address\": \"200 Kent Street\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca\"}}", "contact_information": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"delivery_point\": \"200 rue Kent\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca\", \"country\": \"Canada\"}, \"en\": {\"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0E6\", \"delivery_point\": \"200 Kent Street\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca\"}}", "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-130.880001,36.483355],[-44.478731,36.483355],[-44.478731,61.648267],[-130.880001,61.648267],[-130.880001,36.483355]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "2016-01-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone", "en": "Other Effective Area-Based Conservation Measures"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "https://geoportal.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/FGP/OEABCM/MapServer/0", "name_translated": {"fr": "Autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone", "en": "Other Effective Area-Based Conservation Measures"}, "language": ["en"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}, {"url": "https://geoportal.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/FGP/AMCEZ/MapServer/0", "name_translated": {"fr": "Autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone", "en": "Autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone"}, "language": ["fr"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}, {"url": "https://pacgis01.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/FGPPublic/Oceans_Act_Marine_Protected_Areas/OEABCMs.gdb.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "Autres mesures de conservation efficaces par zone", "en": "Other Effective Area-Based Conservation Measures"}, "language": ["en", "fr"], "resource_type": "dataset", "format": "FGDB/GDB"}], "status": "ongoing", "source_metadata_date_created": "2018-11-02", "topic_category": ["environment", "oceans"], "restrictions": "unrestricted", "aggregate_identifier": "", "responsible_role": "RI_409", "collection": "fgp", "date_published": "2017-05-29", "display_flags": ["fgp_viewer"], "reference_system_information": "3857,EPSG,8.8", "file_id": "44769543-7a23-4991-a53f-c2cf7c7a946f", "license_id": "ca-ogl-lgo", "hierarchy_level": "dataset; jeuDonnées", "owner_org": "dfo-mpo", "metadata_contact": {"fr": "Gouvernement du Canada; Pêches et Océans Canada; Gestion intégrée des océans/Politiques des océans et des pêches/Gestion des écosystèmes et des pêches,carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca", "en": "Government of Canada; Fisheries and Oceans Canada; Integrated Oceans Management/Oceans and Fisheries Policy/Ecosystems and Fisheries Management,613-404-5371,carissa.philippe@dfo-mpo.gc.ca"}}
{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Cet ensemble de données est formé de polygones qui représentent les aires de drainage des stations de débit actives de l’Aire de drainage de la rivière Nelson. En partenariat avec les provinces et territoires et avec d’autres organisations, la Division des relevés hydrologiques du Canada (DRHC) exploite un réseau de plus de 2 600 jauges hydrométriques situées partout au pays. Les polygones du SHN sont une compilation des ensembles de données obtenus de plusieurs organisations participantes, y compris des provinces, des territoires et d’autres ministères. Le personnel d’Environnement et Changement climatique Canada de plusieurs bureaux au pays est aussi responsable de la dérivation de parties importantes de l’ensemble de données. Les utilisateurs doivent savoir que les aires de drainage dérivées de ces polygones pourraient différer des valeurs de superficie brute du bassin versant officielles des stations hydrométriques publiées par la DRHC.", "en": "This dataset consists of a set of polygons that represent the drainage areas of active discharge stations within the Nelson River Drainage Area.  \n  \n  In partnership with the provinces, territories and other agencies, the Water Survey of Canada (WSC) operates a network of over 2600 active hydrometric gauges across the country. The NHS Basin Polygon dataset is compilation of datasets collected from a number of contributing agencies, including provinces, territories and other government departments. Environment and Climate Change Canada staff in a number of offices across the country is also responsible for the derivation of large parts of the dataset. Users should be aware that drainage areas derived from these polygons may differ from official drainage areas of hydrometric stations published by WSC."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "Environment and Climate Change Canada", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "erika.klyszejko@canada.ca", "position_name": {"f