{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Cette carte interactive commémore la participation des Canadiens aux conflits armés en territoire canadien comme à l’étranger. Elle illustre un échantillon d’endroits portant les noms de ceux qui ont servi notre pays. Ces noms commémoratifs nous permettent de ne pas oublier les victimes de guerre, les soldats, les marins, les aviateurs et les civils qui ont été décorés ou qui ont reçu une marque de reconnaissance pour leurs actes de bravoure et le sacrifice ultime au combat. Ces noms soulignent aussi les batailles importantes auxquelles le Canada a participé ainsi que les unités, les régiments, les escadrons et les navires militaires au sein desquels des Canadiens ont servi. Les membres fédéraux, provinciaux et territoriaux de la Commission de toponymie du Canada ont fourni ces noms commémoratifs pour l'élaboration de la carte. Il existe bien d’autres lieux commémoratifs au Canada, et ils seront éventuellement ajoutés à la carte interactive évolutive. Si vous voulez proposer des noms dans le cadre de ce projet, veuillez communiquer avec le Secrétariat de la Commission de toponymie du Canada de Ressources naturelles Canada.", "en": "This interactive map commemorates Canada’s participation in armed conflicts at home and abroad by highlighting a sample of the many geographical features and places named for those that served our country. These commemorative geographical names help us remember war casualties, soldiers, sailors, airmen and airwomen, military leaders, and civilians recognized or decorated for outstanding acts of bravery and sacrifice in battle. These names also commemorate notable battles in which Canada participated, and Canadian military units, regiments, squadrons, and ships in which Canadians served. Federal, provincial and territorial members of the Geographical Names Board of Canada provided these commemorative names for the development of the map. Many more commemorative place names exist in Canada, and will be added in future releases of this evergreen interactive map. If you would like to contribute names to this project, please contact the Geographical Names Board of Canada Secretariat at Natural Resources Canada."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "", "locale": "fra", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "nrcan.geonames-toponymes.rncan@canada.ca", "position_name": {"en": ""}, "frequency": "as_needed", "keywords": {"fr": ["Canada", "CTC", "victimes de la guerre", "Guerre", "Commémoration"], "en": ["Canada", "GNBC", "war casualties", "War", "Commemoration"]}, "ready_to_publish": "true", "id": "ccc75c12-5acc-4a6a-959f-ef6f621147b9", "subject": ["military"], "spatial_representation_type": ["vector"], "distributor": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\", \"organization_name\": \"Gouvernement du Canada; Ressources naturelles Canada; Secteur de la politique strat\\u00e9gique et des r\\u00e9sultats;Centre canadien de cartographie et d\\u2019observation de la terre;Secr\\u00e9tariat de la Commission de toponymie du Canada\", \"phone\": \"\", \"address\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"nrcan.geonames-toponymes.rncan@canada.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"city\": \"\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"organization_name\": \"Government of Canada; Natural Resources Canada; Strategic Policy & Results Sector;Canada Centre for Mapping and Earth Observation;Geographical Names Board of Canada Secretariat\", \"phone\": \"\", \"postal_code\": \"\", \"address\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"nrcan.geonames-toponymes.rncan@canada.ca\"}}", "contact_information": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"\", \"delivery_point\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"nrcan.geonames-toponymes.rncan@canada.ca\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\"}, \"en\": {\"city\": \"\", \"administrative_area\": \"\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"postal_code\": \"\", \"delivery_point\": \"\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"nrcan.geonames-toponymes.rncan@canada.ca\"}}", "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-141.003,41.6755],[-52.6174,41.6755],[-52.6174,83.1139],[-141.003,83.1139],[-141.003,41.6755]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "1867-01-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Carte commémorative du Canada", "en": "Canada’s Commemorative Map"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "https://geoappext.nrcan.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/NRCAN/CCM_CCC_EN/MapServer/0", "name_translated": {"fr": "Carte commémorative du Canada", "en": "Canada’s Commemorative Map"}, "language": ["en"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}, {"url": "https://geoappext.nrcan.gc.ca/arcgis/rest/services/NRCAN/CCM_CCC_FR/MapServer/0", "name_translated": {"fr": "Carte commémorative du Canada", "en": "Canada’s Commemorative Map"}, "language": ["fr"], "resource_type": "web_service", "format": "ESRI REST"}], "status": "completed", "source_metadata_date_created": "2018-11-05", "topic_category": ["intelligence_military"], "restrictions": "unrestricted", "aggregate_identifier": "", "responsible_role": "RI_414", "collection": "fgp", "date_published": "2018-11-02", "display_flags": ["fgp_viewer"], "file_id": "ccc75c12-5acc-4a6a-959f-ef6f621147b9", "license_id": "ca-ogl-lgo", "hierarchy_level": "dataset; jeuDonnées", "owner_org": "nrcan-rncan", "metadata_contact": {"fr": "Gouvernement du Canada; Ressources naturelles Canada; Secteur de la politique stratégique et des résultats;Centre canadien de cartographie et d’observation de la terre,nrcan.fgp-pgf.rncan@canada.ca", "en": "Government of Canada; Natural Resources Canada; Strategic Policy & Results Sector;Canada Centre for Mapping and Earth Observation,voice; 1 (800) 6612638,,nrcan.fgp-pgf.rncan@canada.ca"}}
{"notes_translated": {"fr": "Le Programme d'évaluation de l'état des cultures (PEEC) est conçu et tenu à jour par la Section Télédétection et analyse géospatiale (TAG) de la Division de l'agriculture. Le PEEC regroupe les technologies de télédétection, des SIG et Internet dans le but d'offrir des renseignements fiables, objectifs et à jour sur l'état des cultures et des pâturages sous forme d'une application cartographique sur tout le territoire agricole canadien et le nord des États-Unis.   \n  \n  Deux fois par jour, la National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) saisit une image de toute la surface terrestre à l'aide de satellites dotés d'un radiomètre perfectionné à basse résolution (AVHRR) à un kilomètre de résolution. Ce capteur saisit deux importantes bandes spectrales (le rouge et l'infrarouge) servant à l'observation de la végétation pour produire l'Indice de végétation par différence normalisée (IVDN). Le PEEC permet la visualisation des données AVHRR depuis 1987 pour la plupart des semaines de croissance au Canada, soit entre les semaines juliennes 15 à 41.  \n  \n  Ce jeu de données donne accès à 30 années d’images AVHRR en format GeoTIF et couvre le territoire agricole lors de la saison de croissance des grandes cultures.", "en": "The Crop Condition Assessment Program (CCAP) is developed and maintained by the Remote Sensing and Geospatial Analysis Section (RSGA) within the Agriculture Division. The CCAP combines remote sensing, GIS, and the Internet to provide reliable, objective, and timely information on crop and pasture/rangeland conditions using a mapping application for the whole Canadian agricultural area and the northern portion of the United States.  \n  \n  The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) series of satellites carrying the Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR) records images of the entire Earth's surface twice a day at one kilometre resolution. This detector captures two spectral bands (red and infrared) that have proven to be extremely useful for vegetation monitoring to produce the Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI). CCAP allowed the visualization of AVHRR data since 1987 for most of the growing weeks in Canada, between Julian weeks 15 and 41.  \n  \n  This dataset give access to 30 years of AVHRR images in GeoTIF format and cover all the crops area during the crops growing season."}, "imso_approval": "true", "creator": "INFOSTATS", "locale": "eng", "jurisdiction": "federal", "maintainer_email": "STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca", "position_name": {"fr": "Renseignements généraux", "en": "General enquiries"}, "frequency": "as_needed", "keywords": {"fr": ["Agriculture", "Images satellites", "AVHRR", "IVDN", "Saison de croissance", "Résolution", "PEEC", "Satellite", "Plante", "Statistiques de l'agriculture", "Aide à l'agriculture"], "en": ["Agriculture", "Satellite images", "AVHRR", "NDVI", "growing season", "Resolution", "CCAP", "Satellites", "Plants", "Agriculture statistics", "Agricultural assistance"]}, "ready_to_publish": "true", "id": "44ced2fa-afcc-47bd-b46e-8596a25e446e", "subject": ["agriculture"], "spatial_representation_type": ["grid"], "distributor": "{\"fr\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"organization_name\": \"Gouvernement du Canada; Statistique Canada\", \"phone\": \"1-800-263-1136 (sans frais)\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0T6\", \"address\": \"150, promenade Tunney's Pasture\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\", \"organization_name\": \"Government of Canada; Statistics Canada\", \"phone\": \"1-800-263-1136 (toll free)\", \"address\": \"150 Tunney's Pasture Driveways\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}}", "contact_information": "{\"fr\": {\"city\": \"Ottawa\", \"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"country\": \"Canada\", \"postal_code\": \"K1A 0T6\", \"delivery_point\": \"150, promenade Tunney's Pasture\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\"}, \"en\": {\"administrative_area\": \"Ontario\", \"delivery_point\": \"150 Tunney's Pasture Driveways\", \"electronic_mail_address\": \"STATCAN.infostats-infostats.STATCAN@canada.ca\", \"country\": \"Canada (le)\"}}", "state": "active", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\",\"coordinates\": [[[-143.782063,40.184321],[-46.38161,40.184321],[-46.38161,62.281322],[-143.782063,62.281322],[-143.782063,40.184321]]]}", "time_period_coverage_start": "1987-01-01", "title_translated": {"fr": "Images satellitaires AVHRR (résolution de 1 km) historiques de 1987 à 2017", "en": "Historical AVHRR satellite images (1 km resolution) from 1987 to 2017"}, "type": "dataset", "resources": [{"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/avhrr/AVHRR1KM_1987to1989.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "AVHRR 1km 1987 à 1989", "en": "AVHRR 1 km 1987 to 1989"}, "language": ["en", "fr"], "resource_type": "dataset", "format": "ZIP"}, {"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/avhrr/AVHRR1KM_1990to1994.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "AVHRR 1 km 1990 à 1994", "en": "AVHRR 1 km 1990 to 1994"}, "language": ["en", "fr"], "resource_type": "dataset", "format": "ZIP"}, {"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/avhrr/AVHRR1KM_1995to1999.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "AVHRR 1 km 1995 à 1999", "en": "AVHRR 1 km 1995 to 1999"}, "language": ["en", "fr"], "resource_type": "dataset", "format": "ZIP"}, {"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/avhrr/AVHRR1KM_2000to2004.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "AVHRR 1 km 2000 à 2004", "en": "AVHRR 1 km 2000 to 2004"}, "language": ["en", "fr"], "resource_type": "dataset", "format": "ZIP"}, {"url": "http://ftp.maps.canada.ca/pub/statcan_statcan/avhrr/AVHRR1KM_2005to2009.zip", "name_translated": {"fr": "AVHRR 1 km 2005 à 2009", "en": "AVHRR 1 km 2